ss-entry-simple.content-note: Note: The national currency was formerly the litas (plural litai). Euro notes and coins were introduced in Lithuania on 1 January 2015, at a fixed exchange rate of €1 = 3.45280 litai. The euro and local currency circulated alongside each other until 15 January, after which the euro became the sole legal tender.
